{% set description %}
  Icon only button visually hides the text content of the button. Such a button should be used sparingly and only in places where screen real estate is a concern.
{% endset %}

{% set demo %}
  <bolt-list display="inline" spacing="small">
    <bolt-list-item>
      {% set icon_download %}
        {% include '@bolt-elements-icon/icon.twig' with {
          name: 'download',
        } only %}
      {% endset %}
      {% include '@bolt-elements-button/button.twig' with {
        content: 'File size: 25MB',
        icon_only: icon_download,
        icon_only_tooltip: 'center',
        attributes: {
          type: 'button'
        }
      } only %}
    </bolt-list-item>
    <bolt-list-item>
      {% set icon_add %}
        {% include '@bolt-elements-icon/icon.twig' with {
          name: 'add',
        } only %}
      {% endset %}
      {% include '@bolt-elements-button/button.twig' with {
        content: 'Add another row',
        icon_only: icon_add,
        icon_only_tooltip: 'center',
        attributes: {
          type: 'button'
        }
      } only %}
    </bolt-list-item>
  </bolt-list>
{% endset %}

{% set notes %}
  <bolt-ol>
    <bolt-li>It is recommended that icon only buttons to be used in tandem with tooltip to give the user more context about the button&rsquo;s function.</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li>When writing in plain HTML, <code>aria-label</code> is required to render the button text. For example: <code>&lt;button type="button" class="e-bolt-button e-bolt-button--icon-only" aria-label="Download"&gt;</code>. Text should not be used inside the button when using <code>aria-label</code>.</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li>When writing in plain HTML, <code>&lt;span class="e-bolt-button__icon-center"&gt;</code> is required to wrap around the icon markup. The wrapper ensures that the icon will always center within the button.</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li>Set <code>icon_only_tooltip</code> to create a simple CSS tooltip out of the <code>content</code> data.</bolt-li>
  </bolt-ol>
{% endset %}

{% set twig_markup %}
{% verbatim %}
// Icon only button combined with tooltip
{% set icon_download %}
  {% include '@bolt-elements-icon/icon.twig' with {
    name: 'download',
  } only %}
{% endset %}
{% include '@bolt-elements-button/button.twig' with {
  content: 'File size: 25MB',
  icon_only: icon_download,
  icon_only_tooltip: 'center',
  attributes: {
    type: 'button'
  }
} only %}
{% endverbatim %}
{% endset %}

{% set html_markup %}
{% verbatim %}
// Icon only button combined with tooltip
<bolt-tooltip>
  <button type="button" class="e-bolt-button e-bolt-button--icon-only" aria-label="Download">
    <span class="e-bolt-button__icon-center"><!-- Icon or image markup --></span>
  </button>
  <span slot="content">File size: 25MB</span>
</bolt-tooltip>
{% endverbatim %}
{% endset %}

{% include '@utils/pattern-doc-page.twig' with {
  title: 'Icon Only Button',
  description: description,
  notes: notes,
  demo: demo,
  twig_markup: twig_markup,
  html_markup: html_markup,
} only %}
